@ewencp The better solution is to use the rebalance callback, but it's pretty awkward in code:

``` java
final AtomicBoolean isAssigned = new AtomicBoolean(false);
consumer.subscribe(topics, new ConsumerRebalanceListener() {
  void onAssign(partitions) {
    isAssigned.set(true);
  }
  void onRevoke(partitions) {
    isAssigned.set(false);
  }
}
while (!isAssigned.get())
  consumer.poll(100);

consumer.seekToBeginning()
```

Ouch. If this is a common enough need, maybe we should consider exposing something like `ensureAssignment` which has the same effect.

@granders Looks good now. I'm getting real numbers now, although some of them might need some further investigation.

@hachikuji The code is, in fact, pretty verbose. Shall we file a JIRA to figure out if we should do anything API-wise to make this less ridiculous (especially since if you want to use the rebalance callback for anything else, it'll get significantly messier...)?

